    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-10-16T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-10-16T10:00:00-05:00" n="169"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d169">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.5131/888: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in France (<persName type="from"
                            >Marriner</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-10-16T15:00:00+00:00"
                            >October 16, 1932—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 7:58 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>601. My 600, October 16, noon.<note n="64" xml:id="d169fn64">Not printed.</note>
                    There are indications now that the French wish to prolong the negotiations. This
                    is probably due to their interpretation of Governor <persName corresp="#p_RFD1"
                        >Roosevelt</persName>’s declarations (see my 593, October 11th). The French
                    may consider that if the negotiations can be kept alive until after the
                    elections they will be able either to obtain any benefits of a change of policy
                    or if there is no change to continue the negotiations as if there had been no
                    delay. Evidently if the French intend to delay it will be extremely difficult
                    for the Embassy to obtain rapid or satisfactory action.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Marriner</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
